{
  "stem": "24515.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the refugee committee found these out, 24 hours before my brother was due to sail on the I believe it was, in a very big ship.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they immediately, you know, all the phones to Germany-- hold-- keep this guy out, I mean, he's not a sponsor.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He's, you know, he's nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The lady who was supposed to make the phone call had a son who had the influenza, or something, that day, she didn't come in, and that's how my brother got to England.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Wow.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had quite a bit to do to, you know, to set him up, and to help him, and get him to school, and so on, so on.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had both learned English in school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The trouble with that was that we spoke English grandly-- I got the ones, and As, and so on, but the English didn't.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To be serious about it, English is very easy to learn, the grammar and everything, but it's very, very difficult to speak because it's all idioms, and usages, and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the answer to the question is, well, we-- we knew some words, but we didn't really speak English.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you want me to, I'll tell you some stories about these idioms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing, really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, the parents were as they always were.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There wasn't even much going on in those two-- few months that, you know, he wanted to tell me about.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also, of course, he was a very unhappy kid, to start with.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was put through a very pleasant school, where they tried to look after him, but, I mean, really, he was alone there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, it was pretty damn awful.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
